h2. Request Flow — 8 Steps

|| Step || What Happens || Services Involved ||
| *1. Login* | QA engineer logs in via Cognito. JWT contains team group. Identity Pool grants scoped IAM role. | Cognito, IAM |
| *2. Author* | User types scenario on Agent page. Picks service. Frontend sends to AgentCore. | Amplify, Bedrock AgentCore |
| *3. Plan* | Agent calls get_service_config (DynamoDB), then Claude generates structured test plan with \{service.KEY\} templates. | Bedrock, Claude, DynamoDB |
| *4. Save* | User saves test case. Lambda writes to Aurora with pgvector embedding. | Lambda, Aurora, Bedrock (Titan) |
| *5. Launch* | User clicks Automate. Agent starts ECS Fargate task. Returns noVNC URL. | ECS Fargate, ECR |
| *6. Execute* | Agent connects to Playwright MCP on ECS task. Executes steps in real Chromium browser. Records Playwright calls. | AgentCore, Playwright MCP, ECS |
| *7. View* | User watches live execution via noVNC iframe in browser. | noVNC (WebSocket) |
| *8. Result* | Test completes. Agent returns PASS/FAIL + replay script. Lambda saves run record. ECS task stops. | Lambda, Aurora, ECS |

----

h2. Key Numbers

|| Metric || Value ||
| Total AWS services | 18 |
| UI screens | 4 (Agent, Inventory, Config, Admin) |
| Agent modes | 6 (plan, plan_scenario, start_session, automate, replay, stop_session) |
| Lambda functions | 3 (writer, reader, schema-init) |
| CodePipelines | 3 (agent, lambda, playwright) |
| ECS task specs | ARM64, 2 vCPU, 4 GB RAM |
| Cold start (ECS) | ~60 seconds |
| Execution time (4 steps) | ~30-45 seconds |
| Idle cost | ~$0.50/month |
| Concurrent sessions | 20+ |
